  <prompt>
    Implement the canonical validation contract in `EmailComposer.tsx` + `EmailComposer.reducer.ts`. Replace the stub `validate()` (from task 011) with the real implementation. Wire sub-component validation events (RecipientField, AttachmentList) through the reducer.

    Required canonical error codes (FR-08):
    | Code | Field | Triggered by |
    |---|---|---|
    | `TO_REQUIRED` | `to` | No recipients on send/saveDraft |
    | `TO_INVALID_EMAIL` | `to` | Recipient added with malformed address |
    | `TO_TOO_MANY` | `to` | More than 500 recipients (server cap) |
    | `SUBJECT_REQUIRED` | `subject` | Empty subject on send (not blocking saveDraft) |
    | `BODY_REQUIRED` | `body` | Empty body on send (not blocking saveDraft) |
    | `ATTACHMENT_TOO_LARGE` | `attachments` | Single attachment &gt; 25 MB OR total &gt; 35 MB |
    | `ATTACHMENTS_TOO_MANY` | `attachments` | More than 150 attachments |
    | `ATTACHMENT_BLOCKED_TYPE` | `attachments` | MIME blocked per policy (Wave 6 wires policy; for Wave 1, no blocks) |
    | `FROM_REQUIRED` | `from` | No From address resolved |
    | `FROM_NOT_APPROVED` | `from` | From address not in approved sender list (Wave 2+ enforcement) |

    Return shape: `IValidationResult[] = [{ field, code, message }, ...]` — empty array on success.

    Screen-reader live region (NFR-09): engine renders a hidden `<div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">` near the top. When `validationErrors` populate, populate this region with the error messages (e.g., "Recipients required. Subject required."). Screen reader announces on every change.

    `validate()` is called by:
    - `send()` — blocks on any error
    - `saveDraft()` — blocks on `TO_INVALID_EMAIL` only (allows empty subject/body for drafts)
    - External callers via imperative handle (wizards on step-change)

    Files:
    - Update `EmailComposer.reducer.ts` — `VALIDATION_ERRORS` action, validator function
    - Update `EmailComposer.tsx` — wire `validate()` imperative handle method, render live region, propagate sub-component validation events
    - Update `RecipientField.tsx`, `AttachmentList.tsx` to emit canonical codes via their `onValidationError` callbacks
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React + TypeScript developer; familiar with form-validation patterns + ARIA live regions + typed error contracts.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Engine's `validate()` returns the correct `IValidationResult[]` for all 10 canonical codes. Live region announces validation errors. Send/Save Draft blocked accordingly. Sub-components emit canonical codes (no string-only errors).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-08 + spec MUST rules: NO string-only errors anywhere. Every error has a code from the canonical set.

      Per FR-09 + ADR-019: server-side errors (from `send()` failures) come back as `SendCommunicationError` (Wave 0 task 005) parsed from ProblemDetails. This task handles CLIENT-side pre-send validation only; server-side errors flow separately.

      Per NFR-09: screen-reader live region is a binding accessibility requirement. Live regions use `aria-live="polite"` (or `assertive` if the spec demands immediate announce). Polite is appropriate for validation summaries.
    </background>
