  <steps>
    <step order="1">Update `EmailComposer.types.ts`:
      - Add `EmailComposerValidationCode = 'TO_REQUIRED' | 'TO_INVALID_EMAIL' | 'TO_TOO_MANY' | 'SUBJECT_REQUIRED' | 'BODY_REQUIRED' | 'ATTACHMENT_TOO_LARGE' | 'ATTACHMENTS_TOO_MANY' | 'ATTACHMENT_BLOCKED_TYPE' | 'FROM_REQUIRED' | 'FROM_NOT_APPROVED'`
      - Tighten `IValidationResult.code: EmailComposerValidationCode`</step>
    <step order="2">Update `EmailComposer.reducer.ts`:
      - Add `validateState(state, options: { forSend: boolean }): IValidationResult[]` — pure function returning the array
      - Implements all 10 canonical checks; `forSend=false` skips SUBJECT_REQUIRED + BODY_REQUIRED (allows draft)
      - Add `SET_VALIDATION_ERRORS` action (idempotent set)</step>
    <step order="3">Update `EmailComposer.tsx`:
      - `useImperativeHandle` — `validate: () =&gt; validateState(state, { forSend: true })`; called internally on send
      - `send()` real implementation: run `validateState({forSend: true})`; if errors, dispatch SET_VALIDATION_ERRORS + throw / return early; else call communicationApi `sendCommunication()` with state mapped to request shape
      - `saveDraft()` real implementation: run `validateState({forSend: false})`; if errors, dispatch + return; else POST to draft endpoint or upsert via `sprk_communication` (statuscode=Draft)
      - Render live region: `&lt;div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true" style={visuallyHidden}&gt;{validationErrors.map(e =&gt; e.message).join('. ')}&lt;/div&gt;` near top of composer
      - Visible error display: each validation error rendered next to the relevant field (sub-components consume `validationErrors` filtered by `field`)</step>
    <step order="4">Update `RecipientField.tsx`:
      - When commit produces a TO_INVALID_EMAIL → call `props.onValidationError('TO_INVALID_EMAIL', '...')` with canonical code
      - When recipient count &gt; 500 → emit TO_TOO_MANY</step>
    <step order="5">Update `AttachmentList.tsx`:
      - On cap breach → emit canonical codes (ATTACHMENTS_TOO_MANY, ATTACHMENT_TOO_LARGE)
      - Per-file size &gt; 25 MB → emit ATTACHMENT_TOO_LARGE</step>
    <step order="6">Wire engine's `onValidationError` aggregation to dispatch SET_VALIDATION_ERRORS (merge/dedupe by code).</step>
    <step order="7">Run `npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.</step>
    <step order="7.5">Step 9.5 quality gates — code-review + adr-check (ADR-019, ADR-021, ADR-033).</step>
    <step order="8">Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 020 ✅.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol.</step>
  </steps>

