  <notes>
    The validation contract is the CONSUMER CONTRACT for wizard hosts. A wizard's "Finish" handler:
    ```
    const errors = composerRef.current.validate();
    if (errors.length) { showErrors(errors); return; }
    await composerRef.current.send();
    ```

    Server-side errors (e.g., daily-send-cap hit, Graph rate-limit) come back as `SendCommunicationError` per FR-09 — orthogonal to this client-side contract.

    For Wave 1, ATTACHMENT_BLOCKED_TYPE has no triggers (MIME allow-list ships in Wave 6 task 088). The code is reserved in the union for future enforcement.

    FROM_REQUIRED + FROM_NOT_APPROVED similarly reserved for Wave 2+ approved-sender enforcement; for Wave 1, the From field defaults to the authenticated user and these codes are wire-only (no logic yet).
  </notes>

